### FIX - DPV EU Fundamental Rights Alignment
@prefix eu-rights: <https://w3c-cg.github.io/dpv/2.3/legal/eu/rights#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:Art1_HumanDignity owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:HumanDignity .
:Art2_RightToLife owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:RightToLife .
:Art3_RightToIntegrity owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:PersonalIntegrity .
:Art6_RightToLiberty owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:LibertyAndSecurityOfPerson .
:Art7_PrivateLife owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:PrivateLife .
:Art8_DataProtection owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:DataProtection .
:Art11_FreedomOfExpression owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:FreedomOfExpression .
:Art20_EqualityBeforeLaw owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:EqualityBeforeLaw .
:Art21_NonDiscrimination owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:NonDiscrimination .
:Art23_GenderEquality owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:GenderEquality .
:Art24_RightsOfChild owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:RightsOfChild .
:Art35_HealthCare owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:HealthCare .
:Art41_GoodAdministration owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:GoodAdministration .
:Art47_RightToEffectiveRemedy owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:EffectiveRemedy .
:Art48_PresumptionOfInnocence owl:equivalentClass eu-rights:PresumptionOfInnocence .


### FIX — ODRL Alignment
@prefix odrl: <http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl/2/> .

:Obligation rdfs:subClassOf odrl:Duty ;
    rdfs:comment "An ethics requirement that must be fulfilled. Aligned with ODRL Duty." .

:Permission rdfs:subClassOf odrl:Permission ;
    rdfs:comment "An ethics requirement that permits a specific action under defined conditions. Aligned with ODRL Permission." .

:Prohibition rdfs:subClassOf odrl:Prohibition ;
    rdfs:comment "An ethics requirement that forbids a specific action. Aligned with ODRL Prohibition." .


### FIX — Labels, Definitions and Sources for all classes
@prefix dct: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .

### Core Classes
:Framework rdfs:label "Governance Framework" ;
    rdfs:comment "A governance or regulatory framework defining ethics requirements for AI research." .

:Requirement rdfs:label "Ethics Requirement" ;
    rdfs:comment "A normative statement derived from a governance framework specifying what a researcher must, may, or must not do." .

:Tier rdfs:label "Assessment Tier" ;
    rdfs:comment "Classification of a requirement by its conditionality. Tier 1 requirements are mandatory for all research proposals. Tier 2 requirements are reflective prompts that apply conditionally based on research context." .

:EUCharterRight rdfs:label "EU Charter of Fundamental Rights Article" ;
    rdfs:comment "A fundamental right protected under the Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union (2000/C 364/01)." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Stakeholder rdfs:label "Stakeholder" ;
    rdfs:comment "An individual or organisational role involved in the research ethics assessment process." .

:Evidence rdfs:label "Ethics Evidence Document" ;
    rdfs:comment "A document or artefact that demonstrates compliance with an ethics requirement." .

:RiskCategory rdfs:label "Risk Category" ;
    rdfs:comment "A category of harm or risk that an AI system may cause to individuals, groups, or society." .

:DataCategory rdfs:label "Data Category" ;
    rdfs:comment "A classification of personal or research data relevant to ethics assessment, aligned with GDPR data categories." ;
    dct:source <https://gdpr-info.eu/art-9-gdpr/> .

:Mitigation rdfs:label "Mitigation Measure" ;
    rdfs:comment "A technical or organisational measure that reduces the likelihood or severity of an identified risk." .

:AssessmentProcess rdfs:label "Assessment Process" ;
    rdfs:comment "A formal procedure for evaluating ethics compliance, risk, or impact of a research project or AI system." .

:ComplianceStatus rdfs:label "Compliance Status" ;
    rdfs:comment "The compliance state of a requirement within a given research project assessment." .

:Incident rdfs:label "AI Incident" ;
    rdfs:comment "A documented real-world event in which an AI system caused or contributed to harm, rights violations, or ethical failures." ;
    dct:source <https://www.aiaaic.org/> .

### Framework subclasses
:REAMS rdfs:label "TCD REAMS" ;
    rdfs:comment "Trinity College Dublin Research Ethics Application Management System. Institutional ethics framework for research approval." ;
    dct:source <https://www.tcd.ie/research/ethics/> .

:EUAIAct rdfs:label "EU AI Act" ;
    rdfs:comment "Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 of the European Parliament and of the Council on Artificial Intelligence. FRIA requirements from Article 27." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32024R1689> .

:HorizonEurope rdfs:label "Horizon Europe Ethics Guidelines" ;
    rdfs:comment "European Commission ethics requirements for Horizon Europe funded research projects." ;
    dct:source <https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/horizon/guidance/ethics-appraisal-procedure_he_en.pdf> .

:ACMConference rdfs:label "ACM/NeurIPS Research Ethics Guidelines" ;
    rdfs:comment "Research ethics and broader impact requirements from ACM, NeurIPS, FAccT, AAAI, and ACL Rolling Review conference submission guidelines." ;
    dct:source <https://www.acm.org/code-of-ethics> .

### Requirement subclasses
:Obligation rdfs:label "Obligation" ;
    rdfs:comment "An ethics requirement specifying an action that must be performed. Aligned with ODRL Duty." ;
    dct:source <http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl/2/> .

:Permission rdfs:label "Permission" ;
    rdfs:comment "An ethics requirement specifying an action that is permitted under defined conditions. Aligned with ODRL Permission." ;
    dct:source <http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl/2/> .

:Prohibition rdfs:label "Prohibition" ;
    rdfs:comment "An ethics requirement specifying an action that is forbidden. Aligned with ODRL Prohibition." ;
    dct:source <http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl/2/> .

### Tier subclasses
:Tier1_Mandatory rdfs:label "Tier 1 — Mandatory" ;
    rdfs:comment "Requirements that apply to all research proposals regardless of context. Failure to comply blocks ethics approval." .

:Tier2_Reflective rdfs:label "Tier 2 — Reflective" ;
    rdfs:comment "Requirements that apply conditionally based on research context. Researchers must reflect on whether these apply to their specific project." .

### EU Charter Right classes
:Title1_Dignity rdfs:label "Title I — Dignity" ;
    rdfs:comment "EU Charter of Fundamental Rights Title I covering Articles 1–5 on human dignity." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art1_HumanDignity rdfs:label "Article 1 — Human Dignity" ;
    rdfs:comment "Human dignity is inviolable. It must be respected and protected." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art2_RightToLife rdfs:label "Article 2 — Right to Life" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right to life." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art3_RightToIntegrity rdfs:label "Article 3 — Right to Integrity" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right to respect for his or her physical and mental integrity." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art5_ProhibitionOfSlavery rdfs:label "Article 5 — Prohibition of Slavery" ;
    rdfs:comment "No one shall be held in slavery or servitude." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Title2_Freedoms rdfs:label "Title II — Freedoms" ;
    rdfs:comment "EU Charter Title II covering Articles 6–19 on freedoms." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art6_RightToLiberty rdfs:label "Article 6 — Right to Liberty and Security" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right to liberty and security of person." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art7_PrivateLife rdfs:label "Article 7 — Respect for Private and Family Life" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right to respect for his or her private and family life, home and communications." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art8_DataProtection rdfs:label "Article 8 — Protection of Personal Data" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right to the protection of personal data concerning him or her." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art10_FreedomOfThought rdfs:label "Article 10 — Freedom of Thought" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right to freedom of thought, conscience and religion." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art11_FreedomOfExpression rdfs:label "Article 11 — Freedom of Expression" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right to freedom of expression. This right shall include freedom to hold opinions and to receive and impart information and ideas without interference by public authority." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art16_FreedomToConductBusiness rdfs:label "Article 16 — Freedom to Conduct a Business" ;
    rdfs:comment "The freedom to conduct a business in accordance with Union law and national laws and practices is recognised." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Title3_Equality rdfs:label "Title III — Equality" ;
    rdfs:comment "EU Charter Title III covering Articles 20–26 on equality." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art20_EqualityBeforeLaw rdfs:label "Article 20 — Equality Before the Law" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone is equal before the law." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art21_NonDiscrimination rdfs:label "Article 21 — Non-Discrimination" ;
    rdfs:comment "Any discrimination based on any ground such as sex, race, colour, ethnic or social origin, genetic features, language, religion or belief, political or any other opinion, membership of a national minority, property, birth, disability, age or sexual orientation shall be prohibited." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art22_CulturalDiversity rdfs:label "Article 22 — Cultural Diversity" ;
    rdfs:comment "The Union shall respect cultural, religious and linguistic diversity." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art23_GenderEquality rdfs:label "Article 23 — Equality Between Women and Men" ;
    rdfs:comment "Equality between women and men must be ensured in all areas, including employment, work and pay." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art24_RightsOfChild rdfs:label "Article 24 — Rights of the Child" ;
    rdfs:comment "Children shall have the right to such protection and care as is necessary for their well-being." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art25_RightsOfElderly rdfs:label "Article 25 — Rights of the Elderly" ;
    rdfs:comment "The Union recognises and respects the rights of the elderly to lead a life of dignity and independence." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art26_DisabilityIntegration rdfs:label "Article 26 — Integration of Persons with Disabilities" ;
    rdfs:comment "The Union recognises and respects the right of persons with disabilities to benefit from measures designed to ensure their independence, social and occupational integration and participation in the life of the community." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Title4_Solidarity rdfs:label "Title IV — Solidarity" ;
    rdfs:comment "EU Charter Title IV covering Articles 27–38 on solidarity and social rights." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art31_FairWorkingConditions rdfs:label "Article 31 — Fair and Just Working Conditions" ;
    rdfs:comment "Every worker has the right to working conditions which respect his or her health, safety and dignity." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art35_HealthCare rdfs:label "Article 35 — Health Care" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone has the right of access to preventive health care and the right to benefit from medical treatment under the conditions established by national laws and practices." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art37_EnvironmentalProtection rdfs:label "Article 37 — Environmental Protection" ;
    rdfs:comment "A high level of environmental protection and the improvement of the quality of the environment must be integrated into the policies of the Union." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Title5_CitizensRights rdfs:label "Title V — Citizens' Rights" ;
    rdfs:comment "EU Charter Title V covering Articles 39–46 on citizens' rights." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art38_ConsumerProtection rdfs:label "Article 38 — Consumer Protection" ;
    rdfs:comment "Union policies shall ensure a high level of consumer protection." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art41_GoodAdministration rdfs:label "Article 41 — Right to Good Administration" ;
    rdfs:comment "Every person has the right to have his or her affairs handled impartially, fairly and within a reasonable time by the institutions and bodies of the Union." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Title6_Justice rdfs:label "Title VI — Justice" ;
    rdfs:comment "EU Charter Title VI covering Articles 47–50 on justice." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art47_RightToEffectiveRemedy rdfs:label "Article 47 — Right to an Effective Remedy" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone whose rights and freedoms guaranteed by the law of the Union are violated has the right to an effective remedy before a tribunal." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

:Art48_PresumptionOfInnocence rdfs:label "Article 48 — Presumption of Innocence" ;
    rdfs:comment "Everyone who has been charged shall be presumed innocent until proved guilty according to law." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:12016P/TXT> .

### Risk categories
:PhysicalHarm rdfs:label "Physical Harm" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of bodily injury, death, or physical safety compromise caused by an AI system." .

:PsychologicalHarm rdfs:label "Psychological Harm" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of mental distress, manipulation, coercion, or emotional damage caused by an AI system." .

:FinancialHarm rdfs:label "Financial Harm" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of economic loss, fraudulent debt, or material deprivation caused by an AI system." .

:ReputationalHarm rdfs:label "Reputational Harm" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of damage to an individual's or organisation's reputation through AI-generated outputs or decisions." .

:PrivacyBreach rdfs:label "Privacy Breach" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of unauthorised collection, processing, or disclosure of personal data by an AI system." .

:Discrimination rdfs:label "Discrimination" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of unfair differential treatment of individuals or groups based on protected characteristics by an AI system." .

:EnvironmentalHarm rdfs:label "Environmental Harm" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of negative environmental impact including carbon footprint, resource consumption, or ecological damage from AI systems." .

:DualUseMisuse rdfs:label "Dual-Use Misuse" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk that research or AI outputs intended for beneficial purposes are repurposed for harmful applications." .

:FunctionCreep rdfs:label "Function Creep" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk that an AI system is used beyond its originally defined and ethically approved purpose." .

:WorkplaceSafetyRisk rdfs:label "Workplace Safety Risk" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of harm to workers arising from AI system deployment in occupational settings." .

:DemocraticProcessHarm rdfs:label "Democratic Process Harm" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk of undermining democratic institutions, electoral processes, or civic participation through AI systems." .

:AddictionRisk rdfs:label "Addiction Risk" ;
    rdfs:comment "Risk that AI system design exploits psychological vulnerabilities to create compulsive usage patterns." .

### Evidence types
:Certificate rdfs:label "Certificate" ;
    rdfs:comment "A formal certificate demonstrating completion of a required training or qualification." .

:ConsentForm rdfs:label "Consent Form" ;
    rdfs:comment "A document through which research participants provide informed consent to participate." .

:DataProtectionPolicy rdfs:label "Data Protection Policy" ;
    rdfs:comment "An organisational policy documenting how personal data is collected, stored, and processed in compliance with GDPR." .

:RiskAssessmentReport rdfs:label "Risk Assessment Report" ;
    rdfs:comment "A document identifying and evaluating potential harms arising from a research project or AI system." .

:BiasAssessmentReport rdfs:label "Bias Assessment Report" ;
    rdfs:comment "A document evaluating the presence and extent of bias in an AI system's training data or outputs." .

:DPIA rdfs:label "Data Protection Impact Assessment" ;
    rdfs:comment "A systematic assessment of the privacy risks posed by a data processing activity, required under GDPR Article 35." ;
    dct:source <https://gdpr-info.eu/art-35-gdpr/> .

:FRIA rdfs:label "Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment" ;
    rdfs:comment "An assessment evaluating the impact of an AI system on fundamental rights, as referenced in EU AI Act Article 27." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32024R1689> .

:ModelCard rdfs:label "Model Card" ;
    rdfs:comment "A structured document providing transparency about an AI model's intended uses, performance characteristics, and limitations." .

:DataSheet rdfs:label "Datasheet for Datasets" ;
    rdfs:comment "A structured document describing the composition, collection process, and intended uses of a dataset." .

:EthicsApproval rdfs:label "Ethics Approval" ;
    rdfs:comment "A formal decision by an ethics committee approving a research project to proceed." .

### Assessment processes
:EthicsSelfAssessment rdfs:label "Ethics Self-Assessment" ;
    rdfs:comment "A researcher-completed assessment of the ethical implications of a proposed research project." .

:RiskAssessment rdfs:label "Risk Assessment" ;
    rdfs:comment "A formal process for identifying, analysing, and evaluating risks posed by a research project or AI system." .

:BiasAssessment rdfs:label "Bias Assessment" ;
    rdfs:comment "A systematic evaluation of bias in AI training data, model outputs, or decision processes." .

:FRIAProcedure rdfs:label "Fundamental Rights Impact Assessment Procedure" ;
    rdfs:comment "A structured procedure for assessing AI system impacts on fundamental rights, aligned with EU AI Act Article 27." ;
    dct:source <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX:32024R1689> .

:DPIAProcedure rdfs:label "Data Protection Impact Assessment Procedure" ;
    rdfs:comment "A structured procedure for assessing data protection risks under GDPR Article 35." ;
    dct:source <https://gdpr-info.eu/art-35-gdpr/> .

:EnvironmentalImpactAssessment rdfs:label "Environmental Impact Assessment" ;
    rdfs:comment "A procedure for evaluating the environmental consequences of a research project or AI system deployment." .

### Compliance statuses
:Compliant rdfs:label "Compliant" ;
    rdfs:comment "The requirement is fully satisfied by the research project." .

:NonCompliant rdfs:label "Non-Compliant" ;
    rdfs:comment "The requirement is not satisfied and remediation is required before ethics approval." .

:PartiallyCompliant rdfs:label "Partially Compliant" ;
    rdfs:comment "The requirement is partially satisfied but gaps remain that must be addressed." .

:NotApplicable rdfs:label "Not Applicable" ;
    rdfs:comment "The requirement does not apply to this research project given its specific context and scope." .

